At the same time, almost in all countries where the virtual operator emerged, classic operators tried to protect themselves from this eruption.
The arguments used by these were practically all identical - too small, a market, perhaps too saturated, problems with the quality of service, etc.
In the most advanced countries, however, the regulatory bodies have now intervened and in none of the cases have defended operators but their customers.
Whether with formal measures or informal pressure, they made the first virtual operator emerge and with it began to emerge more.
Unfortunately, the Czech Regulatory Body all of this happens as if it were a burning nail.
We cannot help but be impressed by the confusion of powers in these cases.
But let's not despair.
If this information between behind the scenes is correct and the virtual operator actually gets to these lands, then the Czech market of the mobile phone probably starts moving again.
